# Napster Music — Privacy Policy

Last Updated: May 2026

Napster Music respects your privacy and only stores data required for core bot functionality.

## 1. Data We Store

Napster Music may store:

* Discord user IDs
* Discord server IDs
* channel IDs
* playback history
* queue data
* listening statistics
* premium status
* server music settings

We do NOT store:

* passwords
* Discord tokens
* private messages
* email addresses
* payment information

## 2. Purpose of Data

Stored data is used exclusively for:

* music playback systems
* queue management
* server configuration
* listening analytics
* premium features
* performance and stability monitoring

## 3. Data Sharing

Napster Music does not sell user data.

We do not share stored data with third parties except when required for:

* API functionality
* legal compliance
* infrastructure providers

## 4. Third-Party Services

Napster Music may interact with:

* Discord
* Spotify
* YouTube
* Lavalink providers

Your use of those services is also governed by their respective policies.

## 5. Data Security

Reasonable efforts are made to protect stored data and maintain service stability.

However, no online service can guarantee absolute security.

## 6. Data Removal

Server owners may request removal of server-related data by contacting the developer.

## 7. Policy Updates

This Privacy Policy may change over time. Continued use of Napster Music after updates means you accept the revised policy.
